export const desfsme_title = ["Primary, post primary and special schools - Free school meal entitled pupils"];
export const desfsme_how_do_we_measure = ["Pupils in primary, post primary and special schools entitled to free school meals."];
export const desfsme_source_name = ["School enrolments"];
export const desfsme_source_url = ["https://www.education-ni.gov.uk/topics/school-enrolments"];
export const desfsme_further_information = ["\n1. Figures include pupils in primary (including nursery classes, reception and year 1-7 classes), post primary and special schools. It does not include funded children in voluntary and private preschools nor nursery schools as this data is not available at a pupil level.\n\n2. Ethnic Groups: ‘Other’ includes Irish Travellers. 'White' does not include Irish Travellers.\n\n3. Age is as at 1st July of the previous academic year.\n\n4. FSME figures for pupils in nursery schools/units and pre-schools include parents who are entitled to receive Income Support, or Income-Based Jobseeker's Allowance, or Employment Support Allowance where an award of income-based job-seekers allowance has been converted; or Universal Credit as these are some of the benefits which determine eligibility for free school meals. As school meals are not universally available to children in pre-school education, parental receipt of these benefits is a better indicator of social disadvantage for the pre-school sector. \n\n5. In 2019 changes were made to the SEN register and a medical register was created - <a href='https://www.education-ni.gov.uk/publications/sen-and-medical-categories-guidance-schools'>SEN and Medical Categories - Guidance for Schools.</a>\n\n6. In 2021 changes were made to SEN stages - <a href='https://www.education-ni.gov.uk/publications/de-circular-202106-three-stages-special-educational-provision'>DE Circular 2021/06 - Three Stages of Special Educational Provision.</a>\n\n7. In 2023/24 the school census was impacted by industrial action, due to Action Short of Strike (ASOS). Although data was received from all schools, for 25% of schools (primary, post primary and special schools) pupil level information was not received in electronic format.\nFor those schools refusing to submit electronically, a paper return was received. The result of this was that the Department was unable to obtain all the pupil level information usually received via electronic census returns, for example age, religion, ethnicity and sex. \nIt also meant it was not possible to fully undertake normal validation processes, some validations were inpossible due to a lack of pupil information.\nFurther information can be found in the notes section of the enrolments bulletin - <a href='https://www.education-ni.gov.uk/publications/annual-enrolments-schools-and-funded-pre-school-education-northern-ireland-202324'>Annual enrolments at schools and in funded pre-school education in Northern Ireland 2023/24.</a>"];
export const desfsme_metadata = {dataset : "DESFSME", table_code : "DESCEQ", years : "2018/19 - 2024/25", start_year : "2018/19", end_year : "2024/25", geog_level : "ni", dataset_url : "https://data.nisra.gov.uk/table/DESCEQ", name : "Department of Education", id : "EQGRP FSMSEN", email : "statistics@education-ni.gov.uk", subject : "School enrolments", product : "All schools", title : "Primary, post primary and special schools", note : "Primary, post primary and special schools\n\nHow do we measure this?\n\nFree school meal entitled pupils\nPupils in primary, post primary and special schools entitled to free school meals.\n\nSpecial educational needs pupils with a statement\nPupils in primary, post primary and special schools with a statement of special educational needs (SEN).\n\nSpecial educational needs pupils without a statement\nSpecial educational needs pupils in primary, post primary and special schools without a statement.\n\nTotal enrolment\nAll pupils in primary, post primary and special schools.\n\nSource\n[url=https://www.education-ni.gov.uk/topics/school-enrolments]School enrolments[/url]\nFurther information\r\n\n1. Figures include pupils in primary (including nursery classes, reception and year 1-7 classes), post primary and special schools. It does not include funded children in voluntary and private preschools nor nursery schools as this data is not available at a pupil level.\n\n2. Ethnic Groups: ‘Other’ includes Irish Travellers. 'White' does not include Irish Travellers.\n\n3. Age is as at 1st July of the previous academic year.\n\n4. FSME figures for pupils in nursery schools/units and pre-schools include parents who are entitled to receive Income Support, or Income-Based Jobseeker's Allowance, or Employment Support Allowance where an award of income-based job-seekers allowance has been converted; or Universal Credit as these are some of the benefits which determine eligibility for free school meals. As school meals are not universally available to children in pre-school education, parental receipt of these benefits is a better indicator of social disadvantage for the pre-school sector. \n\n5. In 2019 changes were made to the SEN register and a medical register was created - [url=https://www.education-ni.gov.uk/publications/sen-and-medical-categories-guidance-schools]SEN and Medical Categories - Guidance for Schools.[/url]\n\n6. In 2021 changes were made to SEN stages - [url=https://www.education-ni.gov.uk/publications/de-circular-202106-three-stages-special-educational-provision]DE Circular 2021/06 - Three Stages of Special Educational Provision.[/url]\n\n7. In 2023/24 the school census was impacted by industrial action, due to Action Short of Strike (ASOS). Although data was received from all schools, for 25% of schools (primary, post primary and special schools) pupil level information was not received in electronic format.\nFor those schools refusing to submit electronically, a paper return was received. The result of this was that the Department was unable to obtain all the pupil level information usually received via electronic census returns, for example age, religion, ethnicity and sex. \nIt also meant it was not possible to fully undertake normal validation processes, some validations were inpossible due to a lack of pupil information.\nFurther information can be found in the notes section of the enrolments bulletin - [url=https://www.education-ni.gov.uk/publications/annual-enrolments-schools-and-funded-pre-school-education-northern-ireland-202324]Annual enrolments at schools and in funded pre-school education in Northern Ireland 2023/24.[/url]\n\nSection 75 category: Age\nVariable used: Age\nBreakdown available:: 2-10; 11-15; 16+\n\nSection 75 category: Men and women generally\nVariable used: Sex\nBreakdown available:: Female; Male\n\nSection 75 category: Marital status\nBreakdown available:: These data are not collected by the school census\n\nSection 75 category: Persons with a disability and persons without\nBreakdown available:: These data are not collected by the school census\n\nSection 75 category: Religious belief\nVariable used: Religion\nBreakdown available:: Catholic; Protestant and other Christian religions; Other; No religion; Religion not stated\n\nSection 75 category: Sexual orientation\nBreakdown available:: These data are not collected by the school census\n\nSection 75 category: Persons with dependants and persons without\nBreakdown available:: These data are not collected by the school census\n\nSection 75 category: Racial group\nVariable used: Ethnic Group\nBreakdown available:: White; Other\n\nSection 75 category: Political opinion\nBreakdown available:: These data are not collected by the school census"};
