export const pubb_further_information = ["The source for this indicator is the Northern Ireland Life and Times Survey (NILT) which is an attitudinal survey that takes place at a particular point in the year. One-off events of a particular local or national level occurring during, or close to the survey's fieldwork period may impact results and create volatility from year to year.\r\n\r\nTo account for sampling error, the data have been weighted by age, gender, and location, based on the most recently available Census data.\r\n\r\nIn 2020, the NILT survey was moved from an in-person interviewer-led survey to a combination of CAWI (Computer Assisted Web Interviewing) and CATI (Computer Assisted Telephone Interviewing) - the new format has been used in every year since 2020.\r\n\r\nRespondents to this survey were asked: ‘How important or unimportant is it to you that public bodies like local councils, hospital trusts and government departments take into account the needs of minority ethnic communities?' The figures reported are the proportions who selected 'very important' or 'fairly important'.\r\n\r\nSome figures have been suppressed due to small sample sizes (less than 50 respondents), missing values are denoted as ‘..’ or a blank space depending on the format it is being viewed."];
